HEADWORD: Planing
<hw>Plan"ing</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <def><pos>a. & vb. n.</pos> fr.
<er>Plane</er>, <pos>v. t.</pos></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Planing machine</b></col>. <sd>(a)</sd> <cd>See
<er>Planer</er>.</cd> <sd>(b)</sd> <cd>A complex machine for planing
wood, especially boards, containing usually a rapidly revolving cutter,
which chips off the surface in small shavings as the piece to be planed
is passed under it by feeding apparatus.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Planipennate</ent>⟦br⟧
